This paper deals with search and recommendation systems for fashion e-retail, which involves processing structured data and images to best match customer preference. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of implicit feedback from user behavior, which could fall under the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) or Computer Vision (cs.CV) categories. Finally, the paper also touches on the interplay between customer preference and commercials such as price and promotions, which could relate to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category.
